      "note": "There is no merit in faith in things that you are compelled to acknowledge when they actually happen. Faith is belief in things which you do no see with your eyes but you understand with your spiritual sense: if your whole will consents to it, it results in deeds of righteousness, which are the evidence of your faith (Cf. 10:20)."
